Kennis Music artiste Joel Amadi, aka, Joel has revealed that herdsmen have killed his father in the ongoing crisis in Southern Kaduna that has claimed lots of lives. The artiste who lamented on twitter narrated the sad development calling on the Kaduna State governor and the President to act fast before it becomes difficult to curtail.  “It’s just been confirmed that my lovely Dad is dead-shot by herdsmen and my mom and sisters can’t even talk to me on phone please tag @elrufai he needs to know that he is not doing enough to curb the state of terrorism in Kaduna state.” The singer had previously stated on his Instagram handle Friday that his dad had been abducted by terrorist-herdsmen unleashing violence in the area. “Killing is going on in my father’s village Zikpak, Kafanchan and my Dad has been missing including other villagers are missing and houses are being burnt yet no help. Please repost this till it gets to the governor @elrufai of Kaduna state and the necessary armed forces of Nigeria,” he wrote. Colleagues and fans have continued to express shock on the death of his father while calling on the state and federal government to ensure the protection of lives and properties of the people. 